perspective on issues of central importance in pragmatics, suggesting original ways in which research in the particular areas they adhere to could advance. Apart from the obvious aim of motivating further discussion on the topics it touches on, a central objective of this volume is to underline that research in pragmatics can and does substantially inform research in numerous other fields of enquiry, namely philosophy, cognitive science, linguistics and conversation analysis, revealing in this way the truly interdisciplinary nature of pragmatics theorizing. In this respect, and given that most of the contributions in this volume are from leading scholars in their respective fields, it is clearly expected that the ideas put forth in this volume will have a profound and long-lasting impact for future research in the area.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aIntercultural communicationvCongresses. 0aPragmaticsvCongresses. 4aConversational Analysis. 4aKognitive Linguistik. 4aLinguistics. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPragmatics. 4aPragmatik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAssimakopoulos, Stavros, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2017z9783110547887oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015050270 cprintz978150151430240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150508940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501505089423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501505089.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE